snippet.textDisplay: If you are counting tv shows, they was actually 4 "live action" Spidermans. It starred Nicholas Hammond and only lasted one season. (It wasn't very good.) There was also the live action version on the PBS show The Electric Company. That was actually the first live action version, but I don't really think that should count, as he didn't talk, you never see Peter Parker and they aren't Spiderman stories really. (And there are a couple versions in other countries, but they are not really potraying Peter Parker. So, I would say, as far as the "hero" characters go, four versions of Spiderman, four of Hulk, two Captain Americas, two Quicksilvers, four eight Supermans, eight Batmans (including Pattinson) two Storms, two Cyclops, two Prof X, two Beasts, two Warren Worthington Angels, two Nightcrawlers, two War Machines, and two Colossus', three Daredevils (one in an episode of the hulk show) two Thors for the same reson, two Wonder Women, two Nick Furys, two Blades, There will be a second Spawn, supposedly. snippet.textDisplay: I just had to watch this show & comment right at the beginning of this show. I'll just edit this comment if I want to add anything to it. I just wanted to say I think that having Robert Downey Jr. on your show Joe is totally awesome. I had to watch because he's one of my favorite actors. He's been in some really great movies. Probably one that a lot of people forget was one called ''The Judge'' Robert Downey Jr. plays an attorney & the son of Robert Devall who is still the hometown Judge. Simply a fantastic movie. Robert Downey Jr. was awesome in it to say the least. To see two great iconic actors like Downey & Duvall doesn't happen that often. I can only compare that movie to ''The Mule'' with Bradley Cooper & Clint Eastwood....
